         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/5/67. ¶  ¶ The fruits of Podocarpus Drouyniana, dear Dr Hooker, may give your garden a new conifer. ¶  This species is as yet nowhere in cultivation. The fruit of Nuytsia floribunda I have now for ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>67.05.15a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 268.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/5/67.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The fruits of <name key="Podocarpus%20Drouyniana">Podocarpus Drouyniana</name>, dear Dr Hooker, may give your garden a new conifer.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to [J. Hooker], May 1867 (in this edition as 67-05-00f). M described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Podocarpus%20Drouyniana">Podocarpus Drouyniana</name>
                     </seg> in B64.02.04, p. 86.</p>
               </note> This species is as yet nowhere in cultivation. The fruit of <name key="Nuytsia%20floribunda">Nuytsia floribunda</name> I have now for the first time <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ripe</hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M gave the details of the fruit in B68.12.01, p. 252, under <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Atkinsonia ligustrina</seg>, but slightly differently from the description transcribed below.</p>
               </note> I do not doubt it will germinate! The character of 4 cotyledons appears extraordinar, yet we must not value it too highly, until the cotyledons of many Loranths have been counted.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The text ends on the back of the folio, near the top of the page, without valediction. The text that follows here is filed as f. 19 of the guard-book. It may have been sent at a different time, but is included here on the basis of the mention of four cotyledons.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Nuytsia%20floribunda">Nuytsia floribunda</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Fructus tripterus, fragili-coriaceus (haud crustaceus), pollicem latus (alis inclusis), e[a]s Dodonaearum quarun dam simulans; divisiones formam semirenatam praebentes — Semen unicum, acute trigonum — Albumen amygdalcuum haud sulcatum. Embryo rectus, cylindraceus, fere dimidium albuminis aequans, axilis. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Cotyledones quaternae</hi>
               </seg>, lineari-semicylindricae, circiter ⅔"' longae, radicula vix breviores.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">N. floribunda</seg> was very briefly described in R. Brown (1831), p. 17. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It is described in Bentham (1863-78), vol. 3, p. 387.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Nuytsia%20floribunda">Nuytsia floribunda</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Podocarpus%20Drouyniana">Podocarpus Drouyniana</name>
            </p>
         </div>
